[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_kl67f")
reagent_id = "CaS2"
title = "Carbon disulfide"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]CS₂[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]76 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Liquid[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Colorless[/cell]
[cell]Smell:[/cell][cell]Sweet or unpleasant odor[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
C + 2S → CS₂
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Highly flammable liquid.
• Evaporates easily (volatile).
• Does not dissolve well in water but dissolves many organic substances.
[b]Where it is found[/b]
• Produced industrially from carbon and sulfur at high temperature.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Used as a solvent in industry.
• Used in some chemical manufacturing processes.
[b]Safety[/b]
Toxic and highly flammable.
Vapors can affect the nervous system and should not be inhaled."
